{
  "texts": [
    "AMM aggregators provide flexibility by not requiring specific pairings for transactions, but they can occasionally lead to suboptimal pricing (Park, 2021).",
    "Despite these challenges, DEXs offer an attractive advantage in reducing trading costs, especially for large orders (Lin, 2019).",
    "Finally, market efficiency at CEXs depends on several key factors.",
    "First and foremost, despite their comparative efficiency, CEXs often face constraints, particularly limited trading volume and liquidity.",
    "This can hinder the seamless execution of trades, making them less efficient at handling large order flows (Wang & Krishnamachari, 2022)."
  ]
}